    {
      "question": "If $\\angle ATO = 40^\\circ$ where $T$ is a point outside the circle with center $O$ and $TA$, $TB$ are tangents, find $\\angle AOB$.",
      "answer": "$100^\\circ$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "In $\\triangle OAT$, $\\angle OAT = 90^\\circ$ because the radius is perpendicular to the tangent.",
          "In $\\triangle OAT$, $\\angle AOT = 180^\\circ - (90^\\circ + 40^\\circ) = 50^\\circ$. Since $\\triangle OAT \\cong \\triangle OBT$, $\\angle AOB = 2 \\times \\angle AOT = 100^\\circ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\angle AOT = 180^\\circ - 90^\\circ - 40^\\circ = 50^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB = 2 \\times 50^\\circ = 100^\\circ"
      },
