    {
      "question": "Two concentric circles are of radii $5$ $cm$ and $3$ $cm$. Find the length of the chord of the larger circle which touches the smaller circle.",
      "answer": "$8$ $cm$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $O$ be the center, $AB$ the chord of the larger circle tangent to the smaller circle at $M$. $OM \\perp AB$.",
          "In right $\\triangle OMA$, $OA^2 = OM^2 + AM^2$. Solve for $AM$ and find $AB = 2 \\times AM$."
        ],
        "derivation": "AM = \\sqrt{5^2 - 3^2} = \\sqrt{25 - 9} = \\sqrt{16} = 4 \\text{ cm} \\\\ AB = 2 \\times 4 = 8 \\text{ cm}"
      },
