    {
      "question": "A point $P$ is $13$ $cm$ from the center of a circle. The length of the tangent drawn from $P$ to the circle is $12$ $cm$. Find the radius of the circle.",
      "answer": "$5$ $cm$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $O$ be the center and $A$ be the point of contact. $\\triangle OAP$ is a right-angled triangle.",
          "Apply Pythagoras theorem: $OP^2 = OA^2 + AP^2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "13^2 = r^2 + 12^2 \\\\ 169 = r^2 + 144 \\\\ r^2 = 25 \\\\ r = 5 \\text{ cm}"
      },
